21/05/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Heavy storms have battered parts of Bulgaria, especially the Sofia District, where officials said on Monday (May 21st) that houses, public buildings and schools were flooded, as well as roads.
Two bridges have been swept away by rising river waters and landslides are being reported.
There are no known casualties thus far.
(bTV, BNR, Sega - 21/05/07;
bTV - 20/05/07)
